snippet.textDisplay:
I’ve had COVID before and I’m confused, I’m currently having a cold but this cold is WAY worse than when I had COVID. I know that it only really effects elderly people, but a COLD gave me worse effects than a deadly disease that kills people? It makes no sense, to me at least. Especially since I actually enjoyed having corona because I got to skip school without much consequence.





Anyway… when I had it I just coughed everywhere’s and was tired, so I’m surprised that some of this was actually happening in my body, like dang man
